Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.00,0:00:07.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,译者注：\n本书尚无中文译本，似有民间翻译，但本视频所用翻译均为个人拙译
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.65,0:00:10.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,杜格尔·狄克逊的《人后之人》
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.65,0:00:10.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Man After Man by Dougal Dixon 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.12,0:00:13.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,可谓一部石破天惊的推测进化传奇
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.12,0:00:13.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,is a ground-breaking speculative evolution story 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.47,0:00:17.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其故事纵横五百万年，乃至更久远的未来
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.47,0:00:17.20,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that spans 5 million years and beyond.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.65,0:00:19.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,故事始于24世纪
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.65,0:00:19.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It's the 24th century, 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.95,0:00:25.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,彼时的地球已被污染和人口过剩糟蹋得满目疮痍
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.95,0:00:25.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the Earth has been utterly wrecked by pollution and overpopulation.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:25.60,0:00:32.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,基于此，一小撮“天选之子”得以离开地球，踏上了殖民外星球的征程
Dialogue: 1,0:00:25.60,0:00:32.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,With this, a small number of humans are chosen to leave the Earth in order to colonize other planets.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:32.72,0:00:36.05,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,杰米兹·斯穆特便是其中一员
Dialogue: 1,0:00:32.72,0:00:36.05,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Jimez Smoot is one such example. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.05,0:00:43.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,为了协助建造运载他们的宏伟太空方舟，两个后人类物种应运而生
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.05,0:00:43.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Two post-human species are created to aid in the construction of the great spacecraft that will transport them.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:43.47,0:00:46.87,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它们是“水栖改造人”和“真空改造人”
Dialogue: 1,0:00:43.47,0:00:46.87,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The Aquamorphs and the Vacuumorphs. 
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.87,0:00:50.71,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,前者专为水下作业而生
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.87,0:00:50.71,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The former were designed to live and work under water,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.71,0:00:55.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,后者则被设计用于在毫无空气的寂寥太空中劳作
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.71,0:00:55.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the latter were designed to live and work in the airless void of space.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.25,0:01:02.27,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这些亚种拥有完整的智慧，能够胜任各种繁复的使命
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.25,0:01:02.27,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,These subspecies were fully sapient and able to engage in complicated tasks,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:02.27,0:01:05.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但遗憾的是，他们被剥夺了繁衍后代的能力
Dialogue: 1,0:01:02.27,0:01:05.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but they were bred to be infertile.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.15,0:01:11.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当他们的使命完成后，这些工具人又苟活了一阵子，才最终走向灭亡
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.15,0:01:11.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Once their work had been completed, they lived on for a while before perishing.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.77,0:01:13.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,三百载光阴倏忽而过
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.77,0:01:13.39,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,300 years hence.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.88,0:01:20.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,此时，地球开始渐渐缓过劲来，而人类也分化成了两大阵营
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.88,0:01:20.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,By this point, the Earth is beginning to recover, and two groups of humans have emerged.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.10,0:01:25.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一是选择了田园牧歌式的生活，保留着纯粹人类血脉的“农耕派”
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.10,0:01:25.40,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Those who have adopted a more agrarian lifestyle and remain as pure humans,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.40,0:01:28.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而另一派，则是所谓的“高技术宅”
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.40,0:01:28.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and the other type, the high-techs.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:28.52,0:01:35.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,前者拒斥了高新科技，过着日出而作、日落而息的简朴健康生活
Dialogue: 1,0:01:28.52,0:01:35.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,While the former have effectively shunned advanced technology and lived simple, healthy lives as farmers,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.49,0:01:42.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,后者则因为近亲繁殖和对技术的过度沉迷
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.49,0:01:42.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the latter have come about as a result of inbreeding and over-reliance on technology.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.12,0:01:49.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们的身体孱弱不堪，已然退化，只能蜷缩在机械摇篮里代步
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.12,0:01:49.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They exist in a fragile and degenerate state within mechanical cradles that they use to move around in.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.50,0:01:53.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,真正做到了大门不出，二门不迈
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.50,0:01:53.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They never leave their homes or go outside at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.96,0:01:58.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不过很讽刺，正是这群躯壳虽已腐朽的“高技术宅”
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.96,0:01:58.76,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But they are the ones who, despite their physically weakened state, 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.76,0:02:03.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在不断推进新人类形态的基因创造工程
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.76,0:02:03.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,move forward with the genetic creation of new human forms.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:03.77,0:02:07.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,此时还出现了一群基因工程改造的“水栖人”
Dialogue: 1,0:02:03.77,0:02:07.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Also present are the genetically engineered aquatics, 
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.55,0:02:12.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们的生活方式与那早已灭绝的水栖改造人颇为相似
Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.55,0:02:12.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,beings similar in lifestyle to the now extinct aquamorphs.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:12.30,0:02:16.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这便是“高技术宅”们的开山之作
Dialogue: 1,0:02:12.30,0:02:16.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,These are the first creations of the high-techs.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.32,0:02:22.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,又过了500年，“高技术宅”们的花名册上又添了四大新物种
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.32,0:02:22.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,500 years hence, there are now four additional species created by the high-techs,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.52,0:02:26.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,每一种都是为了适应天差地别的环境而量身打造
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.52,0:02:26.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,each one designed to live in vastly different environments.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.85,0:02:31.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“苔原行者”诞生于寒冷的冰雪之地
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.85,0:02:31.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The tundra-dwellers were made to live in the colder, snowy regions.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.65,0:02:36.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“平原行者”，栖息在干旱之地的茵茵草原
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.65,0:02:36.35,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The plains-dwellers, who live on the grassy plains of arid lands,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.35,0:02:42.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,填补了曾经属于羚羊、角马和水牛的生态位
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.35,0:02:42.02,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,filling the niche left behind by gazelles, wildebeest, and water buffalo.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:42.02,0:02:45.91,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“森林行者”，顾名思义，生活在丛林密布的地区
Dialogue: 1,0:02:42.02,0:02:45.91,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The forest-dweller, of course, lives in forested areas,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.91,0:02:51.85,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,扮演着过去由猿、猩猩和树懒担当的角色
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.91,0:02:51.85,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,filling the roles previously occupied by apes, orangutans, and sloths.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.85,0:02:58.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而“温带林行者”则接管了鹿、熊和狼等动物的职责
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.85,0:02:58.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And the temperate woodland-dweller fills the role of creatures like deer, bears, and wolves.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.55,0:03:06.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,随着这五大物种被播撒到地球各地，人类演化的新航程正式启碇
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.55,0:03:06.12,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,With these five species having been seeded throughout the Earth, humanity's new course can begin.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.12,0:03:11.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,千年弹指一挥间，“高技术宅”们自身也发生了翻天覆地的变化
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.12,0:03:11.50,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,1,000 years hence, the high-tech have themselves changed a great deal.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.50,0:03:18.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们总算甩掉了在“古代”赖以维生的机械摇篮和各种义体
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.50,0:03:18.13,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They have managed to shed the mechanical cradles and body parts that kept them alive in ancient times.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.13,0:03:23.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如今他们的外壳由一坨坨的有机材料构成
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.13,0:03:23.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Their outer shells are now comprised of blob-like organic material,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:23.25,0:03:29.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还会根据时下的流行风尚，随意增减附肢的数量
Dialogue: 1,0:03:23.25,0:03:29.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,with additional limbs being added on or taken away as current fashion dictates.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:29.52,0:03:31.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,五千年后
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.52,0:03:31.90,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,5,000 years hence.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.90,0:03:37.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“温带林行者”已经开始重拾他们失落的智慧
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.90,0:03:37.24,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The temperate woodland-dweller has begun to recover its lost sapience.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.24,0:03:39.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们现在能建造简陋的构筑物
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.24,0:03:39.95,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They can now build rudimentary structures,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.95,0:03:45.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并且点亮了一项奇特的技能，那就是从父母那里继承记忆
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.95,0:03:45.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and have developed the curious ability to inherit memories from their parents.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:45.55,0:03:48.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们成了“记忆传承者”
Dialogue: 1,0:03:45.55,0:03:48.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They have become the memory people.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.52,0:03:53.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,同一时期，还活跃着“平原行者”的后裔
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.52,0:03:53.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Also present during this time are the descendants of the plains-dweller,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.25,0:03:55.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,简称为“迁徙者”
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.25,0:03:55.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,called simply Migrants.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:56.03,0:03:59.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“热带树栖者”也于此刻粉墨登场
Dialogue: 1,0:03:56.03,0:03:59.20,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The tropical tree-dweller has also now come into being,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.20,0:04:02.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们是“森林行者”的后代
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.20,0:04:02.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,itself a descendant of the forest-dweller.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:02.77,0:04:06.03,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不同的演化分支开始显现
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.77,0:04:06.03,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The different branches are beginning to emerge.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:06.35,0:04:09.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一万年后，“苔原行者”们
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.35,0:04:09.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,10,000 years hence, the tundra-dwellers,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.47,0:04:13.19,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以及“温带林行者”的一支后裔
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.47,0:04:13.19,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and a subset of the temperate woodland-dweller descendants,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.19,0:04:16.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,似乎形成了一种共生关系
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.19,0:04:16.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,seem to have formed a symbiotic relationship.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.77,0:04:22.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们分别演变成了“猎手承载者”和“猎手共生体”
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.77,0:04:22.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They have become the hunter-carrier, and the hunter-symbiont, respectively.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.30,0:04:25.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们彼此相处融洽
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.30,0:04:25.43,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They each seem to be comfortable enough with each other,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:25.43,0:04:27.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,亲密无间
Dialogue: 1,0:04:25.43,0:04:27.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,familiar enough with each other,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.38,0:04:29.79,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,到了相依为命的地步
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.38,0:04:29.79,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,to depend on each other for survival.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.79,0:04:33.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,此时还出现了“冬眠者”
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.79,0:04:33.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Also now in existence are the hibernators,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.32,0:04:36.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也是“温带林行者”的后裔
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.32,0:04:36.30,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,descendants of the temperate woodland-dwellers.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:36.30,0:04:41.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,该物种的雄性会在酷寒的冬日里呼呼大睡
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.30,0:04:41.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The males of this species hibernate during the brutally cold winter months.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.26,0:04:45.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“洞穴行者”，同样源自“温带林行者”
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.26,0:04:45.52,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The cave-dweller, another descendant of the temperate woodland-dweller,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.52,0:04:49.33,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,现在盘踞在地下的洞穴和隧道中
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.52,0:04:49.33,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,now populates the subterranean caves and tunnels,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.33,0:04:53.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,只在夜间冒险爬上地表，狩猎觅食
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.33,0:04:53.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,venturing to the surface at night in order to hunt.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.37,0:04:56.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,五万年后
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.37,0:04:56.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,50,000 years hence.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:56.00,0:04:57.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,演化的脚步永不停歇
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.00,0:04:57.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Evolution never stops,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.73,0:05:02.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,三个新物种如今正漫步于林地与平原
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.73,0:05:02.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and three new species are now roaming the woodlands and the plains.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.78,0:05:05.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“岛民”是人类的一个分支
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.78,0:05:05.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The islander is a species of humans,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:05.48,0:05:07.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们的身材嘛，相当娇小
Dialogue: 1,0:05:05.48,0:05:07.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,rather small in stature,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.32,0:05:10.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,居住在热带火山群岛上
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.32,0:05:10.42,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who inhabit the tropical volcanic islands.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:10.72,0:05:14.11,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“寻水者”是一种长得酷似黑猩猩的物种
Dialogue: 1,0:05:10.72,0:05:14.11,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The water-seeker is a chimpanzee-like species
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.11,0:05:18.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们进化出了在广袤大地上侦测水源的本领
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.11,0:05:18.49,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that has evolved to detect water over vast distances.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:18.77,0:05:22.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这两种生物，都脱胎于“温带林行者”
Dialogue: 1,0:05:18.77,0:05:22.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Both of these are descendants of the temperate woodland-dweller.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.60,0:05:26.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“群居平原行者”则是“迁徙者”的后裔
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.60,0:05:26.57,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The communal plains-dweller is a descendant of the migrants,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:26.57,0:05:31.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,算起来，“迁徙者”大概在四万五千年前首次登场
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.57,0:05:31.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who first emerged around 45,000 years before.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.07,0:05:33.63,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,五十万年后
Dialogue: 1,0:05:31.07,0:05:33.63,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,500,000 years hence.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:33.63,0:05:40.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在随后的45万年里，“群居平原行者”还在持续发育
Dialogue: 1,0:05:33.63,0:05:40.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The communal plains-dweller has developed further still in the ensuing 450,000 years,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:40.00,0:05:43.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最终成了一个被称为“社交者”的物种
Dialogue: 1,0:05:40.00,0:05:43.18,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,becoming a species known as the social.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.43,0:05:48.03,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们的手上长出了令人生畏的骨刃，专门用于格斗
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.43,0:05:48.03,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They possess formidable blades on their hands, used for combat.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.30,0:05:51.99,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“舟人”也在这时闪亮登场
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.30,0:05:51.99,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The boat-person has also emerged by this point.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.99,0:05:55.19,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们是“记忆传承者”的进化形态
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.99,0:05:55.19,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,These are an evolved form of the memory people,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:55.19,0:05:58.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,凭借着祖传的记忆，他们学会了造船
Dialogue: 1,0:05:55.19,0:05:58.43,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who use their ancestral memory to build boats
Dialogue: 2,0:05:58.43,0:06:03.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而这些船的样子，和他们智人先祖的造物简直是一个模子刻出来的
Dialogue: 1,0:05:58.43,0:06:03.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that look very much like those of their Homo sapiens forebearers.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:03.57,0:06:06.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,100万年后
Dialogue: 1,0:06:03.57,0:06:06.10,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,1,000,000 years hence.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.10,0:06:11.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“水栖人”进化出了一种新能力，能用一层凝胶状涂层覆盖全身
Dialogue: 1,0:06:06.10,0:06:11.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The aquatics have evolved the ability to cover themselves in a gelatinous coating,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:11.54,0:06:15.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这让他们得以壮着胆子爬上干燥的陆地
Dialogue: 1,0:06:11.54,0:06:15.16,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which allows them to venture out onto dry land.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:15.16,0:06:17.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,看来在他们的血脉深处
Dialogue: 1,0:06:15.16,0:06:17.44,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It would seem that there is something within them
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.44,0:06:23.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,有一种力量在驱使他们，重返其遥远祖先的陆地世界
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.44,0:06:23.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that compels them to return to the Terranian world of their distant ancestors.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:23.07,0:06:26.05,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“水栖人”绝对是值得重点关注的潜力股
Dialogue: 1,0:06:23.07,0:06:26.05,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The aquatics are the ones to watch out for.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.55,0:06:28.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,200万年后
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.55,0:06:28.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,2,000,000 years hence.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.72,0:06:31.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,各种新奇的形态层出不穷
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.72,0:06:31.38,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Various new forms have come into being,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:31.38,0:06:34.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,每一种都有其独特的适应方式
Dialogue: 1,0:06:31.38,0:06:34.22,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,each with its own unique adaptations
Dialogue: 2,0:06:34.22,0:06:38.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以便在这个光怪陆离的未来新地球上生存
Dialogue: 1,0:06:34.22,0:06:38.26,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,for the strange new future Earth that they find themselves in.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.55,0:06:40.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,其中包括“筑巢者”
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.55,0:06:40.60,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,These include the hiver,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:40.60,0:06:42.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们是“社交者”的后裔，个子更高
Dialogue: 1,0:06:40.60,0:06:42.56,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,taller descendants of the socials
Dialogue: 2,0:06:42.56,0:06:47.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因其建造巢穴和拥有蜂巢思维的状态而得名
Dialogue: 1,0:06:42.56,0:06:47.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who get their name from their hive-building and hive-mind state of being.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.65,0:06:49.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还有“寄生者”和“宿主”
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.65,0:06:49.48,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The parasites and hosts,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:49.48,0:06:51.93,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这场面多少有点猎奇
Dialogue: 1,0:06:49.48,0:06:51.93,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,a rather grotesque situation,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:51.93,0:06:54.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但对当事的双方来说似乎还挺受用
Dialogue: 1,0:06:51.93,0:06:54.86,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,but one that seems to work for all concerned.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.28,0:06:56.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“旅行者”
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.28,0:06:56.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The travellers,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:56.25,0:06:58.23,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“舟人”的后代
Dialogue: 1,0:06:56.25,0:06:58.23,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,descendants of the boat people,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:58.23,0:07:02.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们继承了先辈的游牧（游船？）生活方式
Dialogue: 1,0:06:58.23,0:07:02.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who have continued the nomadic lifestyle of their forebears.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:02.67,0:07:03.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最后
Dialogue: 1,0:07:02.67,0:07:03.80,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And finally,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:03.80,0:07:04.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还有“搜寻者”
Dialogue: 1,0:07:03.80,0:07:04.88,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the seeker,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:04.88,0:07:07.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们是从“寻水者”演化而来的
Dialogue: 1,0:07:04.88,0:07:07.73,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,which is descended from the water seeker.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:07.73,0:07:13.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如今“搜寻者”和“筑巢者”之间也建立了一种共生关系
Dialogue: 1,0:07:07.73,0:07:13.25,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,A symbiotic relationship now exists between the seekers and the hivers,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:13.25,0:07:17.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“筑巢者”会利用“搜寻者”作为定位水源的“活体雷达”
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.25,0:07:17.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who utilise the seeker as a means to locate water sources.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:18.07,0:07:20.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,300万年后
Dialogue: 1,0:07:18.07,0:07:20.20,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,3,000,000 years hence.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:20.20,0:07:27.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“树懒人”是“苔原行者”的巨型后裔，专门模仿业已灭绝的大地懒
Dialogue: 1,0:07:20.20,0:07:27.56,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The Slothman is a large descendant of the Tundra Dweller that imitates the now extinct Megatherium.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.56,0:07:33.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们体型庞大、行动迟缓，但仍有其独特的危险之处
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.56,0:07:33.37,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,It is large and heavy, slow, yet still dangerous in its own way.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:33.37,0:07:37.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,尽管他们是在一个没有捕食者的安逸环境中进化而来
Dialogue: 1,0:07:33.37,0:07:37.54,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Despite having evolved in an environment free of predators,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:37.54,0:07:43.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但大自然风云突变，意味着他们现在必须与“刺齿者”共存
Dialogue: 1,0:07:37.54,0:07:43.77,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,shifts in nature have occurred which mean that they must now co-exist with the Spike Tooth.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:43.77,0:07:49.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这是一种酷似剑齿虎的未来人类，已经开始捕食“树懒人”
Dialogue: 1,0:07:43.77,0:07:49.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,This is a Smilodon-like future human that has begun to prey on the Slothmen.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:49.65,0:07:53.31,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但“刺齿者”中那些没经验的“愣头青”自己
Dialogue: 1,0:07:49.65,0:07:53.31,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,But the inexperienced among the Spike Tooths can themselves 
Dialogue: 2,0:07:53.31,0:07:55.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,也可能反过来沦为树懒人的盘中餐
Dialogue: 1,0:07:53.31,0:07:55.36,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,fall prey to the Slothmen,
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.36,0:07:59.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,要是一个不留神，就会被他们庞大的身躯压成肉饼
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.36,0:07:59.32,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,getting crushed by their enormous bulk if they're not careful.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:59.64,0:08:02.62,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“食鱼者”是一种哥布林般的物种
Dialogue: 1,0:07:59.64,0:08:02.62,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The fish-eater is a goblin-like species 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:02.62,0:08:05.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,是“温带林行者”的后代
Dialogue: 1,0:08:02.62,0:08:05.72,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,that is a descendant of the temperate woodland dweller,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:05.72,0:08:07.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“沙漠奔跑者”也是如此
Dialogue: 1,0:08:05.72,0:08:07.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,as is the Desert Runner, 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:07.68,0:08:12.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们因各自环境的压力而走上了截然不同的演化道路
Dialogue: 1,0:08:07.68,0:08:12.82,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,who have diverged greatly due to the pressures of their respective environments.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.82,0:08:17.17,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“树栖者”是“热带树栖者”的深度进化版
Dialogue: 1,0:08:12.82,0:08:17.17,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The Tree Dweller is an involved form of the Tropical Tree Dweller, 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:17.17,0:08:20.51,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,栖息于树上，习性也跟树懒似的
Dialogue: 1,0:08:17.17,0:08:20.51,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and is arboreal and sloth-like.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:20.51,0:08:22.97,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,五百万年后
Dialogue: 1,0:08:20.51,0:08:22.97,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Five million years hence, 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:22.97,0:08:29.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,杰米兹·斯穆特和他那群太空老铁们的后裔，终于回来了
Dialogue: 1,0:08:22.97,0:08:29.00,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the descendants of Jimez Smoot and his space-faring brethren finally return.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:29.00,0:08:32.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，他们早已面目全非，看不出半点人形
Dialogue: 1,0:08:29.00,0:08:32.84,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, they are completely unrecognizable as humans, 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:32.84,0:08:37.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们自己也压根没认出地球是他们的母星
Dialogue: 1,0:08:32.84,0:08:37.55,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and they themselves do not recognize Earth as their place of origin.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.85,0:08:40.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们不觉得这是“荣归故里”
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.85,0:08:40.47,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They don't see it as returning home. 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:40.47,0:08:46.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,只当这是又一颗资源丰富的星球，等着他们来开采和榨干
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.47,0:08:46.67,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They see this world as just another resource-rich planet to mine and ring dry.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:46.67,0:08:53.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们很快便着手基因改造地球上的生物，也就是那些未来人类的后裔
Dialogue: 1,0:08:46.67,0:08:53.14,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,They soon set about genetically modifying the creatures of the Earth, the future human descendants,
Dialogue: 2,0:08:53.14,0:08:57.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,把他们变成了各种奇形怪状的形态，供自己驱使
Dialogue: 1,0:08:53.14,0:08:57.92,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,turning them into grotesque and freakish forms for their own use.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:57.92,0:09:05.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“工程驮兽”被培育出来，并加装了机械部件，用作运输的牲口
Dialogue: 1,0:08:57.92,0:09:05.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The engineered pack animals are bred and augmented with mechanical parts to be used as beasts of burden.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:05.65,0:09:08.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,“食用生物”由“宿主”改造而来
Dialogue: 1,0:09:05.65,0:09:08.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The food creatures are made from the hosts 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:08.68,0:09:13.78,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,被设计成一坨坨肥腻的怪物，专门充当食物来源
Dialogue: 1,0:09:08.68,0:09:13.78,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and designed as blubbery monstrosities that serve as a food source.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:13.78,0:09:18.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而“工程工人”则由“温带林行者”创造
Dialogue: 1,0:09:13.78,0:09:18.86,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And the engineered workers have been created from the temperate woodland dwellers,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:18.86,0:09:26.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,同样被植入了机械零件，用于承担简单的苦力活和操作机器
Dialogue: 1,0:09:18.86,0:09:26.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,themselves also augmented with machine parts to undertake simple tasks and operate machinery.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:26.07,0:09:30.68,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最终，当地球上的一切似乎都已被榨取殆尽时
Dialogue: 1,0:09:26.07,0:09:30.68,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,And eventually, when all had seemingly been extracted from the Earth, 
Dialogue: 2,0:09:30.68,0:09:35.61,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这群星际人类扬长而去，去寻找新的世界加以蹂躏
Dialogue: 1,0:09:30.68,0:09:35.61,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,the interstellar humans left to seek out new worlds to ravage.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:35.61,0:09:40.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然而，他们并没有带走地球所能给予的一切
Dialogue: 1,0:09:35.61,0:09:40.59,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,However, they hadn't taken everything that the Earth had to offer.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:40.59,0:09:46.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在海洋的万丈深渊中，“水栖人”始终未被发现
Dialogue: 1,0:09:40.59,0:09:46.07,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,Deep in the depths of the ocean, the aquatic has remained undetected.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:46.07,0:09:49.01,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,作为唯一幸存的未来人类物种
Dialogue: 1,0:09:46.07,0:09:49.01,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,The sole surviving future human species,
Dialogue: 2,0:09:49.01,0:09:54.65,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这些海牛般的生物似乎蓄势待发，准备有朝一日重返大洋
Dialogue: 1,0:09:49.01,0:09:54.65,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,these manatee-like creatures seem poised to one day re-emerge from the oceans
Dialogue: 2,0:09:54.65,0:10:02.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并在未来的万古岁月中，重新殖民那片曾属于他们遥远祖先的土地
Dialogue: 1,0:09:54.65,0:10:02.15,Default-L2,atg2,0,0,0,,and begin to colonize the surface which belonged to their distant ancestors in the eons to come.
